S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
J O I N T R E S O L U T I O N
RESPECTFULLY REQUESTING A CONVENTION OF THE STATES UNDER ARTICLE V
OF THE UNITED STATES CONSTITUTION
Introduced By: Representatives Corvese, and J. Brien
Date Introduced: January 22, 2025
Referred To: House State Government & Elections
1 WHEREAS, The founders of our Constitution empowered State Legislatures to be
2 guardians of liberty against future abuses of power by the federal government; and
3 WHEREAS, The federal government has invaded the legitimate roles of the States
4 through the manipulative process of federal mandates, most of which are unfunded to a great
5 extent; and
6 WHEREAS, It is the solemn duty of the states to protect the liberty of our people,
7 particularly for the generations to come; and
8 WHEREAS, Article V of the United States Constitution requires the United States
9 Congress to call a convention for proposing amendments upon application of two-thirds of the
10 legislatures of the States for the purpose of proposing amendments to the United States
11 Constitution in order to place clear restraints on these and related abuses of power; now, therefore
12 be it
13 RESOLVED, That this General Assembly, under the provisions of Article V of the
14 Constitution of the United States, hereby petitions the United States Congress to call a
15 Convention for the purpose of proposing amendments to the Constitution of the United States that
16 impose restraints on the federal government, limit the power and jurisdiction of the federal
17 government, and limit the terms of office for its officials and for members of Congress; and be it
18 further
19 RESOLVED, That this General Assembly hereby intends that this be a continuing

1 application considered together with all other passed, pending, and future applications, calling for
2 a convention on the aforementioned concerns of the State of Rhode Island notwithstanding until
3 such time as two-thirds of the several States have applied for a Convention and said Convention
4 is convened by Congress; and be it further
5 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of State be and hereby is authorized and directed to
6 transmit duly certified copies of this resolution to the President and Secretary of the United States
7 Senate; the Speaker and Clerk of the United States House of Representatives; and the Rhode
8 Island Congressional Delegation.
